pull.body:
Adds a new return key to `privatebroadcastinfo` that informs if `privatebroadcast` is being used.

This is motivated by: https://github.com/sparrowwallet/sparrow/issues/1989

Knowing if `privatebroadcast` is set can be useful for some external software like Sparrow to avoid call `getprivatebroadcastinfo` each time to see if broadcast was done through that.

```bash
sliv3r@sliv3r-tuxedo:~/Documentos/Projectes/BitcoinCore/bitcoin$ ./build/bin/bitcoin-cli -testnet4 getprivatebroadcastinfo
{
  "private_broadcast_enabled": false,
  "transactions": [
  ]
}
sliv3r@sliv3r-tuxedo:~/Documentos/Projectes/BitcoinCore/bitcoin$ ./build/bin/bitcoin-cli -testnet4 getprivatebroadcastinfo
{
  "private_broadcast_enabled": true,
  "transactions": [
  ]
}

```

